      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "\\b[a-z0-9]{30,80}\\b",
        "message": "Plaid secret detected in source code. Secrets are private keys used to authenticate API requests to Plaid. Exposing these credentials allows attackers to access Plaid API endpoints, retrieve users' bank account data, read transaction history, access account balances, obtain identity information, and perform income verification requests. Compromised secrets can lead to mass financial data breaches affecting all users. Rotate secrets immediately if exposed and implement secure credential storage using environment variables, AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault, or Azure Key Vault.",
