      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(?:plaid_client_id|plaidClientId|PLAID_CLIENT_ID|client_id|clientId)\\s*[=:]\\s*['\"][a-f0-9]{24,30}['\"]",
        "message": "Plaid client ID explicitly assigned in source code. This high-confidence detection indicates a Plaid client identifier hardcoded in a variable assignment or configuration statement. Client IDs authenticate applications with Plaid services and when combined with secrets enable unauthorized API access. Hardcoding credentials makes rotation difficult and exposes OAuth2 configuration details. Remove hardcoded values immediately and replace with environment variables (PLAID_CLIENT_ID) or secure configuration management. Check adjacent code for potential secret exposure requiring immediate rotation.",
