      {
        "type": "regex",
        "pattern": "(?:plaid_secret|plaidSecret|PLAID_SECRET|plaid_api_secret|plaidApiSecret|PLAID_API_SECRET|secret|client_secret)\\s*[=:]\\s*['\"][a-z0-9]{30,80}['\"]",
        "message": "Plaid secret explicitly assigned in source code - CRITICAL SECURITY ISSUE. This detection indicates a Plaid private key hardcoded in source code. Secrets are the most sensitive Plaid credential type and enable full API access to retrieve users' financial data, transaction history, account balances, identity information, and income verification. Exposed secrets allow attackers to access all user accounts connected through your Plaid integration. This represents a critical security vulnerability. IMMEDIATE ACTIONS REQUIRED: 1) Remove hardcoded secret from source code, 2) Rotate credentials through Plaid Dashboard immediately, 3) Implement secrets management (AWS Secrets Manager, HashiCorp Vault, Azure Key Vault), 4) Audit all API access logs for unauthorized usage, 5) Review adjacent code for additional credential exposure.",
